1 Visit site WebAssembly Explorer.
https://mbebenita.github.io/WasmExplorer/

2 Write you code in c++ with some function for export
something like this

int myfunction(int i) {

  return (int)i+2;
}

3
Compile and download WASM file like demo.wasm

4
For security reasons you need launch your pages from web server
Install apache
sudo apt install apache2
Test apache localhost
http://localhost/

5 Copy test wasm inside folder /var/www/ of your website

sudo cp test.wasm /var/wwww/

6 Open Console log for quick test
Inspect, Console

fetch('test.wasm').then(res=>res.arrayBuffer()).then(buf=>WebAssembly.instantiate(buf))
After promise fulfilled
Then make it "Store as global variable" 
temp0


